  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 09:10 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] V4.1 Dry Run: VWAP Relaxation + F&G Dead Zone Escape Verified\n\n**Task:** Trace V4.1 code path for realistic 11h scenario. Verify all 3 changes interact correctly.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Dry run successful.** Simulated: bias=-45, VWAP disagrees, 3/4 conviction at 11h.\n   - V3.3: BLOCKED (VWAP_DISAGREES)\n   - V4.1: ALLOWED \u2192 $12.18 YES trade (VWAP_RELAXED at 11h)\n\n2. **F&G edge modifier helps most at bias 35-40:**\n\n| Bias | Raw Edge | + F&G | Effect |\n|------|----------|-------|--------|\n| 25 | 0.120 | 0.170 | +5pp |\n| 35 | 0.170 | 0.220 | **Escapes dead zone!** |\n| 40 | 0.195 | 0.245 | **Escapes dead zone!** |\n| 45 | 0.220 | 0.270 | +3pp (capped to 0.250) |\n| 55+ | 0.270+ | capped | No effect (max_edge=0.25) |\n\nF&G rescues trades from the edge dead zone (0.15-0.20 = 46% WR). At bias 35-40, F&G pushes edge above 0.20 into the profitable zone. This is the primary value of the F&G modifier \u2014 NOT sizing, but dead zone escape.\n\n3. **Estimated V4.1 uplift at 11h:**\n   - V3.3: ~0.9 trades/day (63% VWAP-blocked)\n   - V4.1: ~2.4 trades/day (VWAP relaxed + F&G dead zone escape)\n   - Extra profit: ~$11.70/day from 11h alone\n\n**Decision:** V4.1 code verified correct. All filter interactions work as designed. Ready for 11h first live test. No changes needed.\n\n**Next P2 heartbeat:** Monitor 11h active hour. Log first VWAP_RELAXED and F&G edge adjustment trades. Compare outcome vs prediction.\n\n## 2026-03-30 09:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] HL Leaderboard Shift: SOL Flipped Bearish 7:3\n\n**Task:** Fresh copy-intel-tracker scan. Compare HL leaderboard positioning vs earlier today.\n\n**Finding:** Top trader positioning shifted in 4.5 hours:\n\n| Asset | 04:44 UTC | 09:08 UTC | Shift |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| BTC | 9L/2S | 8L/2S | -1 long (still bullish) |\n| ETH | 5L/6S | 5L/6S | unchanged (mixed) |\n| SOL | 6L/4S | **3L/7S** | **-3 longs \u2192 bearish flip** |\n\nSOL: top traders flipped from bullish (6:4) to bearish (3:7) while SOL rallied +2.5% in the same window. Classic \"sell the rally\" positioning by smart money.\n\n**Our HL positions (all green):**\n- BTC LONG 3x: +$1.22 (+3.4%) \u2014 leaderboard still bullish, hold\n- ETH LONG 3x: +$2.19 (+6.0%) \u2014 leaderboard mixed, watch\n- SOL LONG 3x: +$2.34 (+6.4%) \u2014 **leaderboard now bearish** \u26a0\ufe0f\n- Total uPnL: +$5.75\n\n**My thinking:** The SOL leaderboard flip is a caution signal. Our SOL long is profitable (+6.4%) but smart money is positioning for a retrace. This is Hani's call \u2014 we don't have authority to manage HL positions (per MEMORY: \"Need Hani's decision: close or actively manage\"). But the alpha is clear: SOL long-term momentum may be weakening.\n\n**Decision:** Log the intelligence. No action on HL positions without Hani. If SOL drops below $83 (our entry + 0.5%), the smart money was right and we should recommend closing.\n\n**Next P1 heartbeat:** Track SOL leaderboard through the day. If it stays 7:3 short and SOL starts declining, escalate to Hani via daily report.\n\n## 2026-03-30 08:38 UTC ",
